message.content: {"value":{"title":"A First Spark","rating":4,"summary":"In this debut fantasy, a young wizard discovers latent power and is whisked away to a prestigious wizarding school. The tale blends classic school-year rhythms with an inventive magic system built on runes and resonance, allowing the protagonist to grow from unsure newcomer to a confident wielder of his abilities. The book shines in its character work—firm friendships, mentoring figures, and a believable arc of self-discovery—and in its world-building, where spellcraft feels tangible and the setting is richly imagined. A lurking conspiracy adds tension beyond the classroom, expanding the stakes beyond adolescence. While some tropes feel familiar and the middle act lags a little, the prose remains engaging and the emotional throughline—identity, responsibility, and the cost of power—lands with sincerity. A strong start to a promising series for fans of coming-of-age fantasy with a magic-school backdrop."}}
